00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:20,720
我们只需要到二十三层
We just have to make it to the 23rd floor.

208
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:24,790
二十三层有个通风口 能把我们带到那帮人那儿
There's an access door to the air system there that'll take us up to where these guys are.

209
00:11:24,890 --> 00:11:28,520
看吧 都说了我们会想到办法的
See? Told you we'd come up with a plan.

210
00:11:31,690 --> 00:11:32,460
嘿
Hey.

211
00:11:32,490 --> 00:11:33,860
你脸上怎么有迪斯科花纹
What's with the disco face?

212
00:11:33,890 --> 00:11:35,660
你想说什么
Got something to tell me?

213
00:11:35,700 --> 00:11:37,600
因为通讯被堵住了
Since the signals are now being jammed,

214
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:41,450
这栋楼里所有的紧急电话都打出不去 
every emergency call being placed in this building is bouncing back to me

215
00:11:41,450 --> 00:11:42,870
所以都转给了我
because they can't get out.

216
00:11:42,910 --> 00:11:46,110
接电话 也许我们能知道一些信息
Answer the calls. We might get some information.

217
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:47,860
你好
Hello?

218
00:11:47,860 --> 00:11:52,760
谢天谢地 我需要警察帮助 我在办公室里 刚才发生了爆炸

219
00:11:52,820 --> 00:11:58,580
别着急女士 我知道了 警察正在赶来的路上

220
00:11:58,620 --> 00:12:00,490
请您先移步至二楼

221
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:02,550
你这是搞什么
What are you doing?

222
00:12:02,690 --> 00:12:03,950
在葡萄牙文化中
In the Portuguese culture,

223
00:12:03,950 --> 00:12:06,660
已经证明女性的声音在危机时刻
it is proven that people find a woman's voice more soothing

224
00:12:06,690 --> 00:12:08,430
更能舒缓情绪
in moments of crisis.

225
00:12:09,030 --> 00:12:10,760
- 你好 - 你好
- Hello? - Hello.

226
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,930
我是约翰・肯尼思探长
I'm Detective John Kennex.

227
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:16,430
我是个性格怪异的电子警察
I'm an automated police officer with a very difficult personality.

228
00:12:16,460 --> 00:12:17,500
是911吗
911?

229
00:12:17,530 --> 00:12:18,970
请保持冷静
Please remain calm.

230
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,600
我...我这里有一个枪手
I'm... I'm trapped with a gunman.

231
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:22,230
请帮帮我
Please help.

232
00:12:22,370 --> 00:12:24,470
没事的 请深呼吸
Everything's all right. Just take a breath.

233
00:12:24,510 --> 00:12:25,700
你叫什么名字
What is your name?

234
00:12:26,500 --> 00:12:27,970
我叫佩吉
It's Paige.

235
00:12:28,410 --> 00:12:29,270
你好 佩吉
Hi, Paige.

236
00:12:30,380 --> 00:12:31,940
你能跟我们说说这枪手吗
What can you tell me about the gunmen?

237
00:12:31,980 --> 00:12:33,380
我不知道
I don't know.

238
00:12:33,620 --> 00:12:36,830
我妹妹在他们手上
They have my sister...

239
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:38,480
还有其他人
and others.

240
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:39,720
听着 佩吉
Listen, Paige,

241
00:12:39,750 --> 00:12:40,920
我现在就在这栋大厦里
I'm in the building.

242
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:42,950
你要回答我几个问题
I need to ask you a few questions,

243
00:12:42,990 --> 00:12:45,360
但首先我要知道的是 你现在安全吗
but first I need to know... are you safe?

244
00:12:45,390 --> 00:12:46,960
你现在没有被劫持是吗
Are you out of harm's way?

245
00:12:47,990 --> 00:12:49,300
我想是的
I think so.

246
00:12:49,330 --> 00:12:51,730
- 目前为止 - 很好 听我说
- For now. - Okay, listen to me.

247
00:12:51,770 --> 00:12:53,700
你现在在哪 你在第几层
Where are you? What floor are you on?

248
00:12:53,740 --> 00:12:55,630
我在二十五层
I'm on the 25th floor.

249
00:12:55,670 --> 00:12:58,840
我藏在储藏室里
I'm in the utility closet.

250
00:13:01,870 --> 00:13:03,040
接下来
Next face.

251
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:05,050
你 跪下
You, on your knees.

252
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:06,980
跪下
On your knees!

253
00:13:07,010 --> 00:13:08,350
不 不 不要
Oh, no, no!

254
00:13:08,380 --> 00:13:09,810
噢 天呐
Oh, God.

255
00:13:13,910 --> 00:13:15,050
佩吉
Paige?

256
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:16,480
佩吉 发生什么事了
Paige, what's happening?

257
00:13:17,250 --> 00:13:19,150
他们杀了他
They've shot him.

258
00:13:19,490 --> 00:13:21,490
卢死了
Lou is dead.

259
00:13:30,970 --> 00:13:32,900
嘿 小兵 给我拿点水
Hey, dogface. Water.

260
00:13:38,910 --> 00:13:40,740
是一具尸体
We got a body!

261
00:13:52,110 --> 00:13:53,860
条子滚开

262
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:53,950
不要让人群接近
Keep those people back!

263
00:13:54,690 --> 00:13:57,390
那些混蛋 他们到底想怎样
Those bastards. What do they want?

264
00:13:59,290 --> 00:14:01,630
保罗探员 启动人质援救方案
Detective Paul, initiate hostage protocol.

265
00:14:01,660 --> 00:14:02,950
给他们送通讯工具 
Send them the comm.

266
00:14:03,370 --> 00:14:04,900
给他们送通讯工具
Send them the comm!

267
00:14:11,010 --> 00:14:13,490
让遥控飞机升空 我们必须和他们谈判
Get that drone in the air. We've got to start negotiating.

268
00:14:23,890 --> 00:14:25,490
通讯工具到了
Comm's here.

269
00:14:37,610 --> 00:14:38,980
你是谁
What's your name?

270
00:14:39,010 --> 00:14:40,340
马尔多纳多队长
Captain Maldonado.

271
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:42,010
你怎么称呼
And you are?

272
00:14:42,040 --> 00:14:45,410
我可以告诉你 不过我不想让你的努力白白浪费
Well, I'd tell you, but I don't want to nullify your efforts.

273
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:47,980
既然我们已经引起了你的注意
Now that we have your attention...

274
00:14:48,510 --> 00:14:50,640
我们有几个要求
we have some demands.

275
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:56,170
佩吉 你可以把电话举起来让我听听他们在说什么吗
Paige, can you hold the phone up so I can hear what's going on?

276
00:14:56,910 --> 00:14:59,200
我真的不想再把人质扔出去了
I really hate to throw out any more hostages.

277
00:14:59,470 --> 00:15:01,610
我们就有话直说吧 如何
Let's get down to brass tacks, huh?

278
00:15:01,640 --> 00:15:02,950
你想怎么样
What do you want?

279
00:15:02,980 --> 00:15:04,140
第一
First,

280
00:15:04,180 --> 00:15:06,210
让你的狙击手从屋顶撤离 
get your snipers off the roof,

281
00:15:06,210 --> 00:15:09,120
然后告诉那些集合在楼下待命的人
and tell those men you have assembled out front to stand down,

282
00:15:09,150 --> 00:15:11,250
让他们远离这座大厦
and keep them away from the building,

283
00:15:11,290 --> 00:15:14,990
否则还会有人质从天而降
or hostages will continue to fall from the sky.

284
00:15:19,890 --> 00:15:22,500
告诉保罗探员让他的人撤离
Tell Detective Paul to have his men stand down.

285
00:15:23,430 --> 00:15:25,540
B队 撤退
Bravo team, stand down.

286
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:30,720
都走了
All clear.

287
00:15:32,220 --> 00:15:33,050
好了
Done.

288
00:15:33,380 --> 00:15:34,520
还有什么
What else?

289
00:15:34,550 --> 00:15:37,210
我们要三架垂直起降飞机在屋顶待命 
We'd like three v-tols on the roof standing by,

290
00:15:37,210 --> 00:15:39,150
确保我们安全到达边境
clear airspace from here to the border,

291
00:15:39,190 --> 00:15:43,610
最后 我要一个裂变触发器
and finally, I'd like one fission igniter delivered to me, please.

292
00:15:44,750 --> 00:15:46,830
那是军用武器
That's military-grade technology.

293
00:15:46,860 --> 00:15:48,530
我无权支配
I don't have that authority.

294
00:15:48,560 --> 00:15:51,130
那我建议你联系有这个权限的人
Well, then I suggest you contact someone who does.

295
00:15:55,300 --> 00:15:57,970
面部识别成功
Facial recognition identified.

296
00:16:06,020 --> 00:16:07,580
你现在听我说 卢卡斯
Now, you listen to me, Lucas,

297
00:16:08,220 --> 00:16:09,920
如果你想让我跟你合作
if you want me to cooperate with you,

298
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:12,020
那么你也要配合我
I need you to cooperate with me.

299
00:16:12,060 --> 00:16:14,590
你手上有多少人质
How many hostages do you have?

300
00:16:15,530 --> 00:16:19,450
多到如果他们死了 你的饭碗就保不住了
More than enough to end your career if they die.

301
00:16:19,470 --> 00:16:21,600
你还有四十三分钟
You have 43 minutes.

302
00:16:23,570 --> 00:16:26,280
定时器设为四十三分钟 让鲁迪・洛姆来见我
Set the timer for 43 minutes, and get me Rudy Lom.

303
00:16:31,710 --> 00:16:32,750
喂
Hello?

304
00:16:32,780 --> 00:16:33,880
你还在吗
Are you there?

305
00:16:34,220 --> 00:16:35,720
我在 佩吉
Right here, Paige.

306
00:16:35,750 --> 00:16:37,360
有人来救我们吗
Is anyone coming?

307
00:16:37,390 --> 00:16:38,420
你要撑住
You just hang tight.

308
00:16:38,450 --> 00:16:40,360
我们马上就去救你
We're gonna be with you real soon.

309
00:16:40,390 --> 00:16:42,230
你听到他们的对话了吗
Did you hear the phone call?

310
00:16:42,270 --> 00:16:44,070
是的 我听到了 谢谢你
Yeah, I did. Thank you.

311
00:16:44,100 --> 00:16:46,240
不要挂断 我马上回来
Just hold on a second. I'll be right back.

312
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:50,880
裂变触发器真有我想的那么危险吗
Is a fission igniter as bad as I think it is?

313
00:16:50,910 --> 00:16:53,620
这是一个大型爆炸装置的触发系统
It's a trigger mechanism for a large explosive device.

314
00:16:53,650 --> 00:16:55,220
百万吨级别
Megaton level.

315
00:16:55,250 --> 00:16:56,580
百万吨
Megaton.

316
00:16:58,920 --> 00:17:00,220
佩吉 你在吗
Paige, you there?

317
00:17:00,250 --> 00:17:03,550
你能告诉我他们手上有多少人质吗
Can you tell me how many hostages they've got up there?

318
00:17:04,250 --> 00:17:06,290
二十五个左右
25 or so.

319
00:17:06,320 --> 00:17:08,260
至少在这个房间是这样
At least in this room.

320
00:17:08,290 --> 00:17:10,260
我看不太清楚
It's hard for me to see.

321
00:17:10,290 --> 00:17:11,860
你做得很好 佩吉
You're doing great, Paige.

322
00:17:11,900 --> 00:17:13,130
你妹妹怎么样
How's your sister?

323
00:17:13,360 --> 00:17:15,400
都是我的错
This is all my fault.

324
00:17:15,430 --> 00:17:18,460
要不是我她就不会在这
She wouldn't be here if it wasn't for me.

325
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:20,700
她从镇子上来
She's visiting from out of town.

326
00:17:20,730 --> 00:17:24,370
只是路过这里 想和我吃午饭
She just stopped by to have lunch...

327
00:17:24,410 --> 00:17:26,900
可现在她却要独自面对这些
and now she's all alone.

328
00:17:26,940 --> 00:17:29,740
佩吉 你能告诉我有多少持枪的人吗
Paige, can you tell me how many gunmen there are?

329
00:17:29,980 --> 00:17:33,680
他们一直走来走去 我不知道
People keep coming and going; I don't know.

330
00:17:33,710 --> 00:17:36,850
至少...五六个
Five... six, at least.

331
00:17:36,890 --> 00:17:38,450
但应该更多
But there were more.

332
00:17:40,820 --> 00:17:43,090
对不起 我做不到
I'm sorry, I can't do this.

333
00:17:43,130 --> 00:17:44,930
我太害怕了
I'm so scared.

334
00:17:47,930 --> 00:17:49,830
佩吉 你以前冰钓过么
Paige, you ever been ice fishing?

335
00:17:51,870 --> 00:17:52,940
没
No.

336
00:17:52,970 --> 00:17:54,710
我十一岁的时候
When I was 11 years old,

337
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:58,510
我爸带我去麦克法兰湖冰钓
my dad took me ice fishing to Lake McFarland.

338
00:17:59,140 --> 00:18:01,720
准备回家的时候 突然间
We were coming back, and all of a sudden

339
00:18:01,750 --> 00:18:05,550
冰面裂开了 我正好掉进去
the ice cracked, and I went right under.

340
00:18:05,590 --> 00:18:08,290
我看不见 也无法呼吸
I couldn't see, I couldn't breathe.

341
00:18:08,330 --> 00:18:10,430
我以为我就要死了
I thought I was gonna die.

342
00:18:10,970 --> 00:18:17,340
湖水非常冷 像无数根针在扎我的全身一样
The water was so cold, it was like thousands of needles stinging every part of my body.

343
00:18:17,370 --> 00:18:19,940
就在那时我爸跳了下来
And then my dad jumped in,

344
00:18:19,970 --> 00:18:23,040
他抓住我 把我往岸上拖
and he grabbed me and started dragging me back to shore.

345
00:18:23,070 --> 00:18:24,810
你想让她睡着么
Are you trying to put her to sleep?

346
00:18:26,480 --> 00:18:29,540
即使我们还没脱离危险
And even though we were still in a lot of danger,

347
00:18:29,580 --> 00:18:31,190
我却感觉很安全
I felt safe.

348
00:18:31,220 --> 00:18:32,620
我觉得
I felt like...

349
00:18:32,650 --> 00:18:34,990
一切都会好的
everything was gonna be okay,

350
00:18:35,020 --> 00:18:37,120
因为我不是一个人
because I wasn't alone.

351
00:18:37,460 --> 00:18:39,390
佩吉
Paige...

352
00:18:39,430 --> 00:18:41,120
你不是孤身一人
you're not alone.

353
00:18:41,660 --> 00:18:43,390
我会陪着你
I'm with you.

354
00:18:43,420 --> 00:18:46,560
一切都会没事的
Everything is gonna be okay.

355
00:18:48,620 --> 00:18:50,430
你相信我么
Do you believe me?

356
00:18:52,340 --> 00:18:53,800
我相信
Yeah, I do.

357
00:18:54,340 --> 00:18:55,880
很好 好姑娘
All right, good girl.

358
00:18:55,910 --> 00:18:58,010
你要坚持下去
You just hang in there.

359
00:19:04,590 --> 00:19:05,720
保罗
Yeah. Paul.

360
00:19:05,760 --> 00:19:07,750
肯尼思和多利安有什么消息么
Any sign of Kennex and Dorian?

361
00:19:07,790 --> 00:19:08,950
目前还没有
Uh, nothing so far.

362
00:19:09,190 --> 00:19:10,110
让你的人留在原地 
Keep your men back,

363
00:19:10,110 --> 00:19:12,990
在每扇窗户和每个出口 布置好遥控飞机和侧位仪
but I want drones and spotters on every window and exit.

364
00:19:13,030 --> 00:19:14,890
我要知道我的人现在怎么样了
I want to know what's happening with my men.

365
00:19:14,930 --> 00:19:16,230
好的 没问题 长官
Yeah, you got it, Captain.

366
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:20,570
我不可能拿到裂变触发器
There's no way I can get a fission igniter.

367
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:27,540
如果有种方法能在给足他们要求的同时
What if there was a way to give them what they wanted

368
00:19:27,580 --> 00:19:29,780
还能拖住他们呢
and stall them at the same time?

369
00:19:29,820 --> 00:19:31,050
你有什么主意
What have you got?

370
00:19:31,080 --> 00:19:32,720
我可以做一个假的
I could build a replica.

371
00:19:33,250 --> 00:19:34,850
万一他们认出来了呢
What if they can spot a fake?

372
00:19:34,890 --> 00:19:37,720
我做的可以通过扫描
I can make one that will pass a scan.

373
00:19:37,760 --> 00:19:40,560
但如果他们检查出来了 或者直接就用了
If they test it out or try and use it immediately,

374
00:19:40,600 --> 00:19:41,750
那我们就都完了
then we're out of luck.

375
00:19:42,230 --> 00:19:43,790
我们可以冒这个险
That's risk we'll have to take.

376
00:19:43,840 --> 00:19:44,930
我们开始吧
Let's get started.

377
00:19:46,430 --> 00:19:47,800
- 长官 - 怎么了
- Captain?  - Yep?

378
00:19:47,830 --> 00:19:51,770
卢卡斯・文森特是神圣开拓军队的高级特务
Lucas Vincent... he's a high-level operative in the Holy Reclamation Army,

379
00:19:52,110 --> 00:19:54,250
那是一个分散式的恐怖组织
a decentralized network of terrorist cells

380
00:19:54,280 --> 00:19:57,180
具有反西方倾向 有劫持人质的记录
with anti-Western bias and a history of hostage taking,

381
00:19:57,210 --> 00:19:59,080
没有人质有好下场
none of them ending well.

382
00:19:59,120 --> 00:20:01,420
去年八月他们劫持了东京附近的大使馆
Last August they took over an embassy near Tokyo.

383
00:20:01,450 --> 00:20:03,680
使用相同的手段 强行闯入
Same MO... they enter with force,

384
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:05,850
引起媒体和执法机关的注意
drew the attention of the media and law enforcement

385
00:20:05,890 --> 00:20:08,220
通过挟持人质达到他们的目的
using human hostages as collateral for their demands.

386
00:20:08,260 --> 00:20:09,340
然后呢 
What happened?

387
00:20:09,340 --> 00:20:12,060
他们帮助他们的人逃出了监狱
They facilitated the release of several of their comrades.

388
00:20:12,090 --> 00:20:15,190
只要得到他们想要的 他们就会放人
Once they got what they wanted, they released the hostages.

389
00:20:15,220 --> 00:20:17,590
但是他们不害怕杀人
But they're not afraid to take lives...

390
00:20:17,630 --> 00:20:19,290
包括自己的命
including their own.

391
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:26,680
你知道么 每个人都会被楼梯绊倒
You know, everyone trips on stairs,

392
00:20:26,700 --> 00:20:30,910
经统计大概每上2222个阶梯就发生一回
and it's calculated to occur in one in every 2,222 occasions.

393
00:20:30,940 --> 00:20:32,680
真有趣
That's very interesting.

394
00:20:32,710 --> 00:20:34,980
- 你知道什么才是更有趣的么 约翰 - 什么
- You know what would be interesting, John? - What?

395
00:20:35,010 --> 00:20:37,610
就是你再给我讲一遍冰钓的故事
If you told me that ice fishing story again.

396
00:20:52,320 --> 00:20:55,350
如果你想保持身材 我们可以每周末都去做越障训练
If you want to get in shape, we can run the O-course every weekend.

397
00:20:55,390 --> 00:20:57,090
喔 真的能么
O-can we?

398
00:21:07,180 --> 00:21:08,550
分头行动
Let's split up.

399
00:22:31,890 --> 00:22:33,650
多利安 你还好么
Dorian, you okay?

400
00:22:34,790 --> 00:22:36,290
约翰 快过来
John, get over here.

401
00:22:48,770 --> 00:22:50,100
这层没人了
Floor's clear.

402
00:22:52,240 --> 00:22:53,430
你还好么
You okay?

403
00:22:53,460 --> 00:22:55,190
你脑袋破了
You took one to the head.

404
00:22:55,460 --> 00:22:57,570
没错 被弹回来的子弹打到了
Yeah, ricochet.

405
00:22:59,010 --> 00:23:00,620
你找到什么了
Whatcha got?

406
00:23:00,980 --> 00:23:02,100
我也不确定
I'm not sure.

407
00:23:02,140 --> 00:23:03,540
但是这上写了字
But there's writing on it.

408
00:23:03,570 --> 00:23:04,510
"开始"
"Start."

409
00:23:04,540 --> 00:23:07,210
- 开始 - 开始
- Start? - Start.

410
00:23:08,610 --> 00:23:09,910
你查出他的身份了么
You I.D.'d him?

411
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:17,080
他叫迈克尔・多纳瑞
His name is Michael Demerais.

412
00:23:17,120 --> 00:23:19,250
他是神圣开拓军队的一员
He's a member of the Holy Reclamation Army.

413
00:23:19,280 --> 00:23:21,120
这就是幕后黑手
So they're behind this.

414
00:23:24,100 --> 00:23:25,520
也许不是
Maybe not.

415
00:23:32,730 --> 00:23:34,600
这是个变脸器
It's a facemaker.

416
00:23:39,270 --> 00:23:40,940
所以 这人是谁
So who's this guy?

417
00:23:42,810 --> 00:23:44,540
他叫格雷戈・斯通
His name is Gregor Stone.

418
00:23:44,580 --> 00:23:46,380
他有持枪抢劫的案底
He has a few priors for armed robbery.

419
00:23:46,410 --> 00:23:49,820
他们为什么要装成激进组织的成员
Why would they impersonate members of a radical organization?

420
00:23:51,230 --> 00:23:52,380
怎么了
What's wrong?

421
00:23:53,090 --> 00:23:56,320
我的动态电压调节被子弹摧毁了
My dynamic voltage scaling has been damaged by the bullet.

422
00:23:56,560 --> 00:23:58,860
你能说的简单一点么
You want to say that a little less complicated?

423
00:23:58,890 --> 00:24:01,400
五分钟后我将不能走路
I won't be able to walk in five minutes.

424
00:24:09,260 --> 00:24:11,160
我们的飞机呢
Where are our v-tols?

425
00:24:11,290 --> 00:24:12,760
我正在努力
I'm working on it.

426
00:24:18,670 --> 00:24:21,000
根据它发出的信号的频率
Based on the frequency at which these transmit...

427
00:24:21,030 --> 00:24:23,770
我测出这楼里有七个变脸人
I detect seven facemakers in the building.

428
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:26,200
如果想隐藏他们的身份
If they hide their identities,

429
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:28,070
带个面具不是更方便
why not just wear a mask?

430
00:24:28,280 --> 00:24:30,350
为什么要伪装成别人
Why pretend to be something else?

431
00:24:30,430 --> 00:24:32,100
这个问题问的好
That's a good question.

432
00:24:41,140 --> 00:24:42,410
好了
All right.

433
00:24:42,940 --> 00:24:44,770
让我来试试修修你
Let's try and fix you.

434
00:24:48,320 --> 00:24:49,510
伤口看起来怎么样
How does it look?

435
00:24:50,240 --> 00:24:52,650
没什么大碍
Yeah, it's, uh, totally fine.

436
00:24:52,680 --> 00:24:54,140
几乎都看不到它
You can hardly see it.

437
00:24:54,190 --> 00:24:55,320
好吧
Okay.

438
00:24:55,550 --> 00:24:56,820
那我要怎么做
So, what do I do?

439
00:24:56,850 --> 00:24:59,150
有一条品红色的肌腱
All right, there's a magenta colored tendon.

440
00:24:59,180 --> 00:25:00,860
我需要你切掉它
I need you to cut it.

441
00:25:02,520 --> 00:25:04,920
等下 这...这东西干净吗
All right, is... is that thing clean?

442
00:25:05,150 --> 00:25:06,320
当然干净
Of course it is.

443
00:25:07,160 --> 00:25:08,220
你确定吗
Are you sure?

444
00:25:08,260 --> 00:25:09,460
确定
Positive.

445
00:25:12,500 --> 00:25:13,460
该死
Damn it.

446
00:25:13,510 --> 00:25:15,200
- 我说的是品红色 - 它是品红色的
- I said magenta. - It was magenta.

447
00:25:15,240 --> 00:25:16,740
- 我说的是品红色 那是淡紫色 - 该死的品红
- I said magenta. That was lavender. - The hell's magenta?

448
00:25:16,770 --> 00:25:18,600
这里面有五十种色调的紫色
There's 50 shades of purple in there.

449
00:25:18,640 --> 00:25:20,340
我告诉你了 那是条淡紫色的
I'm telling you, that was the lavender one.

450
00:25:20,380 --> 00:25:22,340
- 不 不 好了 等一下 - 怎么了
- No, no. Okay, wait a minute. - What?

451
00:25:22,380 --> 00:25:23,610
- 你拿着这东西干嘛 - 切点电线啊
- What are you doing with that? - Gotta cut the wire.

452
00:25:23,650 --> 00:25:25,480
这东西不能进入我的脑袋
That's not going inside of my head.

453
00:25:25,510 --> 00:25:27,390
- 我是你的搭档 相信我 - 如果鲁迪在这
- I'm your partner, trust me. - If Rudy were here,

454
00:25:27,420 --> 00:25:29,370
他肯定对你有很大的意见
he'd have a really big issue with you right now.

455
00:25:29,390 --> 00:25:30,650
- 约翰... - 有些情况比这还糟糕
- John... - Look, it could always be worse.

456
00:25:30,700 --> 00:25:32,590
- 约翰 统计... - 你会没事的
- John, the statistics... - You're going to be fine.

457
00:25:36,530 --> 00:25:37,710
多利安
Dorian?

458
00:25:51,490 --> 00:25:53,560
请别这样看着我
Please stop looking at me like that.

459
00:25:54,490 --> 00:25:57,360
离你交付假的裂变装置还有五分钟
You have five minutes to deliver the decoy fission device.

460
00:25:57,390 --> 00:26:00,200
我已经尽快在做了
I'm working as fast as I can.

461
00:26:02,440 --> 00:26:05,080
四分四十五秒
Four minutes, 45 seconds.

462
00:26:05,110 --> 00:26:07,810
完美是不能计时的
You can't put a clock on perfection.

463
00:26:07,850 --> 00:26:11,630
很明显 设计你的礼仪芯片的人当时很仓促
Clearly someone was rushing when they designed your manners chip.

464
00:26:19,360 --> 00:26:20,830
约翰 你还在吗
John, are you there?

465
00:26:21,660 --> 00:26:23,130
我可以听到你 佩吉
I can hear you, Paige.

466
00:26:23,170 --> 00:26:24,700
他们移动了
They've moved.

467
00:26:24,730 --> 00:26:26,840
他们老去拐角的窗户
They keep going to a corner window...

468
00:26:26,870 --> 00:26:28,680
做些什么
doing something.

469
00:26:28,710 --> 00:26:30,140
他们在做什么
What are they doing?

470
00:26:30,170 --> 00:26:32,380
我不知道
I don't know.

471
00:26:34,580 --> 00:26:38,290
我妹妹...她在哭
My sister... she's crying.

472
00:26:38,320 --> 00:26:40,950
其中一个看守 他总在看她
And one of the guards, he keeps looking at her.

473
00:26:42,490 --> 00:26:45,160
佩吉 我保证我马上就去救你 
Look, I promise I'll get to you soon, Paige.

474
00:26:45,200 --> 00:26:47,400
你妹妹叫什么名字
What's your sister's name?

475
00:26:47,440 --> 00:26:48,870
詹娜
Jenna.

476
00:26:48,900 --> 00:26:50,210
詹娜
Jenna?

477
00:26:50,240 --> 00:26:52,370
她的中间名是格特鲁德
Her middle name's Gertrude.

478
00:26:52,410 --> 00:26:54,240
这名字够汉子
Ooh, that's rough.

479
00:26:52,410 --> 00:26:54,240
Gertrude这个名字的含义是"军队的力量"

480
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:56,280
你的中名叫什么
What's yours?

481
00:26:56,310 --> 00:26:59,050
不 不 不 我不告诉你
Oh, no. No, no, we're not doing that.

482
00:26:59,980 --> 00:27:01,650
快点 告诉我
Come on, tell me.

483
00:27:05,780 --> 00:27:08,730
好吧 但你最好不要告诉别人 好吗
All right, but you better not tell anyone, okay?

484
00:27:08,760 --> 00:27:10,860
这是警察的命令
Police orders.

485
00:27:12,270 --> 00:27:13,920
雷金纳德
It's Reginald.

486
00:27:14,130 --> 00:27:16,540
我爸是艾尔顿・约翰的脑残粉
My dad was a big Elton John fan.

487
00:27:16,770 --> 00:27:18,140
谁
Who?

488
00:27:18,170 --> 00:27:20,800
艾尔顿・约翰 他是过去的一名歌手
Elton John. He's an old-time singer.

489
00:27:20,850 --> 00:27:23,140
据说 他的真名是雷金纳德
Apparently, his real name was Reginald.

490
00:27:26,350 --> 00:27:27,050
你还好吧
You okay?

491
00:27:30,220 --> 00:27:31,350
真恶心
Gross.

492
00:27:31,390 --> 00:27:32,690
但还好
But good.

493
00:27:33,420 --> 00:27:35,060
有情况
Something's happening.

494
00:27:35,160 --> 00:27:36,620
过来帮忙
Get over here and help.

495
00:27:37,270 --> 00:27:39,860
其中一个枪手
One of the gunmen,

496
00:27:39,900 --> 00:27:41,010
他受伤了
he's hurt.

497
00:27:41,030 --> 00:27:42,280
谁打伤的你
Who shot you?

498
00:27:42,470 --> 00:27:43,940
有两个男人在这楼里
There are two men in the building.

499
00:27:43,970 --> 00:27:45,480
是条子吗
Cops?

500
00:27:45,510 --> 00:27:46,850
我不知道
I don't know.

501
00:27:47,380 --> 00:27:48,990
格雷戈在哪
Where's Gregor?

502
00:27:49,020 --> 00:27:50,520
我们走散了
We got separated.

503
00:27:50,560 --> 00:27:51,890
你想让我们去找他吗
Do you want us to look for him?

504
00:27:51,930 --> 00:27:53,530
不
No.

505
00:27:53,560 --> 00:27:54,990
调更多的人去楼梯间
Put more men on the stairwell.

506
00:27:55,030 --> 00:27:56,600
不让任何人上这层楼
No one gets up on this floor.

507
00:27:56,640 --> 00:27:59,200
去 你 去
Go. You, go.

508
00:27:59,240 --> 00:28:01,880
约翰 他们知道你在这楼里
John, they know you're in the building.

509
00:28:01,910 --> 00:28:05,940
他们派了几个拿着枪的人去守着楼梯
They sent a couple guys with giant guns to guard the stairs.

510
00:28:07,610 --> 00:28:09,110
就算你上来了
Even if you do get up here,

511
00:28:09,150 --> 00:28:10,610
你怎么进的来呢
how are you gonna get in?

512
00:28:10,950 --> 00:28:12,350
相信我 佩吉
Trust me, Paige.

513
00:28:12,380 --> 00:28:14,250
我们会找到路来救你的
We'll find a way to get to you.

514
00:28:18,530 --> 00:28:20,490
我对你很失望啊 马尔多纳多队长
I'm disappointed in you, Captain Maldonado.

515
00:28:20,500 --> 00:28:22,490
我还以为我们处的很好
I thought we were getting along so well.

516
00:28:22,530 --> 00:28:24,660
我不知道你在说什么
I don't know what you're talking about.

517
00:28:24,700 --> 00:28:26,600
我说撤掉条子
I said no cops.

518
00:28:28,570 --> 00:28:30,040
我已经召回了我的人
I pulled my men back.

519
00:28:30,070 --> 00:28:34,080
我的人都在大楼外面 疏散人群
The only people I have there are conducting the evacuation, outside the building.

520
00:28:35,410 --> 00:28:39,110
那你怎么解释我的人刚在楼下杀了两个警察
Then how do you explain the two cops my men just killed downstairs?

521
00:28:40,810 --> 00:28:42,920
他在唬人
He's bluffing.

522
00:28:44,320 --> 00:28:45,430
我不知道你杀了什么人
I don't know what men you killed,

523
00:28:45,460 --> 00:28:47,230
但他们不是我的人
but they weren't mine.

524
00:28:48,960 --> 00:28:50,160
我们有约在先
We made a deal.

525
00:28:50,200 --> 00:28:52,710
我给你想要的条件 没有人会死
I get you what you want, no one else dies.

526
00:28:59,730 --> 00:29:02,940
我什么时候能拿到我的裂变触发器
When do I get my fission ignitor?

527
00:29:05,210 --> 00:29:07,220
已经在路上了 十分钟以内到
It's on its way, ten minutes or less.

528
00:29:07,250 --> 00:29:12,190
很好 多一分钟你就会在人行道上多看到一具尸体
Great. Every minute longer is another body you'll be scraping off the pavement.

529
00:29:25,560 --> 00:29:28,170
闭上你的嘴
Keep your mouth shut.

530
00:29:33,670 --> 00:29:34,800
约翰
John?

531
00:29:36,300 --> 00:29:37,800
我要出去
I'm going out there.

532
00:29:37,830 --> 00:29:40,000
我不能让詹娜一个人面对
I can't leave Jenna alone.

533
00:29:41,030 --> 00:29:42,730
佩吉 那是个不明智的做法
Paige, that's a bad idea.

534
00:29:42,760 --> 00:29:44,670
我必须那么做
I have to. I have to.

535
00:29:44,700 --> 00:29:46,030
我们再有几层楼就到了
We're a few floors away.

536
00:29:46,070 --> 00:29:47,500
她需要我
She needs me.

537
00:29:48,030 --> 00:29:50,140
我需要她
I need her.

538
00:29:50,370 --> 00:29:57,180
如果我们会死...我也要和她在一起
If we're gonna die... ...I want to be with her.

539
00:29:57,710 --> 00:30:00,250
她是我妹妹
She's my sister.

540
00:30:02,450 --> 00:30:04,780
现在是我唯一可以混进人群里的机会
Now is my only chance to blend in

541
00:30:04,820 --> 00:30:06,210
而他们不会发现我
without anyone seeing me.

542
00:30:06,250 --> 00:30:08,020
佩吉 呆在那别动
Paige, just stay where you are.

543
00:30:08,050 --> 00:30:09,320
我会开着机
I'll leave my phone open.

544
00:30:09,350 --> 00:30:11,020
你会听到我们的对话
You'll be able to hear what's going on.

545
00:30:11,060 --> 00:30:12,190
佩吉 太冒险了
Paige, it's too risky.

546
00:30:12,220 --> 00:30:13,990
听着 别动
Listen to me, just stay put.

547
00:30:14,020 --> 00:30:15,390
我必须这样做
I have to.

548
00:30:15,420 --> 00:30:17,190
- 我必须这样做 - 佩吉 拜托了
- I have to. - Paige, please,

549
00:30:17,220 --> 00:30:19,120
佩吉 听我的 佩吉
just listen to me. Paige.

550
00:30:19,160 --> 00:30:22,170
佩吉 你在听吗 佩吉
Paige, are you there? Paige?

551
00:30:45,050 --> 00:30:46,720
我在
I'm here.

552
00:30:47,450 --> 00:30:48,670
没事的
It'll be okay.

553
00:30:54,540 --> 00:30:55,800
保罗探员
Detective Paul?

554
00:30:55,830 --> 00:30:58,200
收到 触发器已经可以传送
Copy. The ignitor is ready for delivery.

555
00:30:58,230 --> 00:30:58,930
快点
Come on.

556
00:30:58,970 --> 00:31:01,010
快 快 速度
Come on, come on, speed it up.

557
00:31:03,390 --> 00:31:04,260
长官 准备好了
It's good to go, sir.

558
00:31:04,300 --> 00:31:06,100
好 听你命令
Okay, waiting on your order.

559
00:31:07,600 --> 00:31:08,900
传送
Send it.

560
00:31:08,930 --> 00:31:10,270
送她上去
Let's get her up.

561
00:31:27,790 --> 00:31:28,790
舆洗室

562
00:31:36,520 --> 00:31:38,060
打扰一下
Excuse me.

563
00:31:38,790 --> 00:31:40,630
我要去下洗手间
I have to go to the bathroom.

564
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:46,970
你想要我尿在地上 是么
You're not going to make me pee on the floor, are you?

565
00:31:48,410 --> 00:31:50,170
给你三十秒
You've got 30 seconds.

566
00:31:51,100 --> 00:31:53,440
嗨 老大
Hey, boss...

567
00:31:53,480 --> 00:31:55,310
又有东西送上来了
we're getting another delivery.

568
00:32:06,730 --> 00:32:08,020
遥控飞机到了
The drone's coming.

569
00:32:08,080 --> 00:32:09,750
通话中

570
00:32:30,550 --> 00:32:32,190
卢卡斯 我们有约在先
We had an agreement, Lucas.

571
00:32:32,220 --> 00:32:34,160
我们真诚地给了你想要的东西
We've operated in good faith here.

572
00:32:34,190 --> 00:32:36,230
我相信你做到了
I believe in honoring a deal.

573
00:32:36,260 --> 00:32:37,400
准备
Stand by.

574
00:32:38,430 --> 00:32:41,430
等我们放了人质我会通知你的
I'll let you know how we're gonna release the hostages.

575
00:32:44,730 --> 00:32:46,240
希望能骗过他们
Let's hope they buy it.

576
00:32:46,670 --> 00:32:49,140
现在把这个消息发给其他人
Send the message to the other crew now.

577
00:32:50,200 --> 00:32:51,550
他们应该准备好了
They should be ready.

578
00:32:51,770 --> 00:32:53,540
是时候结束这场战争了
It's time to wind this up.

579
00:32:54,570 --> 00:32:56,110
什么其他人
What other crew?

580
00:32:56,150 --> 00:32:58,010
或许还有更多他们的人在这栋楼里
Maybe there are more of them in the building.

581
00:32:58,040 --> 00:33:00,810
- 或许他们在楼外面 - 但干扰器还开着
- Maybe they're outside the building. - But the jammer's still on.

582
00:33:00,810 --> 00:33:03,620
除非他们有人在外面 不然他们不可能和别人通话
If they have people outside, they wouldn't be able to talk to each other.

583
00:33:04,650 --> 00:33:07,020
除非他们用别的通话方式
Unless they were talking some other way.

584
00:33:15,890 --> 00:33:17,530
开始
"Start."

585
00:33:27,980 --> 00:33:30,440
他们肯定是用它来和某人近距离的在大楼里进行
They must be using it as some sort of point-to-point communication

586
00:33:30,480 --> 00:33:32,210
某种点对点的通讯 
with someone in proximity of the building.

587
00:33:32,210 --> 00:33:34,450
佩吉说那个头目
Paige said the man in charge...

588
00:33:34,480 --> 00:33:36,280
一直走到窗边
kept going to the window.

589
00:33:47,990 --> 00:33:49,470
我没想到他们能搞来这个
I didn't think they'd come through.

590
00:33:50,300 --> 00:33:52,330
如果这是追踪装置呢
What if there's a tracking device?

591
00:33:52,580 --> 00:33:54,270
反正我们不带走它
We're not taking it anyway.

592
00:33:54,300 --> 00:33:56,210
没关系
It doesn't matter.

593
00:34:00,210 --> 00:34:02,610
他不想要那个装置 说不通啊
He doesn't want the tech. That doesn't make sense.

594
00:34:03,920 --> 00:34:06,920
为什么挟持人质然后和我们要一个不想带走的装置
Why take hostages and negotiate for tech you don't want?

595
00:34:06,960 --> 00:34:08,660
或许这是调虎离山
Maybe it's a diversion.

596
00:34:08,690 --> 00:34:10,630
对啊 但为了什么
Yeah, but for what?

597
00:34:14,230 --> 00:34:15,270
在临近建筑物里有什么
Are there any targets

598
00:34:15,300 --> 00:34:17,370
更有价值的目标是他们想要的么
of value in the adjacent buildings?

599
00:34:20,780 --> 00:34:22,210
唯一有价值的目标就是
The only target of any value is

600
00:34:22,250 --> 00:34:25,380
专门研究钯的重金属称重站了
a precious metal weigh station specializing in palladium.

601
00:34:27,150 --> 00:34:28,420
他们想抢劫
It's a heist.

602
00:34:28,460 --> 00:34:31,390
钯 那就值得他们做这么多了
Palladium. That would make all this worthwhile.

603
00:34:50,350 --> 00:34:51,180
包起来
Wrap it up.

604
00:34:51,210 --> 00:34:52,680
我们只有十分钟
We're out of here in ten.

605
00:35:06,730 --> 00:35:08,450
丹尼尔 坚持住
Hang in there, Daniel.

606
00:35:09,300 --> 00:35:12,470
当这结束后 我们就已经在某处的海滩上了
When this is over, we'll all be on a beach somewhere,

607
00:35:12,510 --> 00:35:14,210
你也会完好如初的
you'll be as good as new.

608
00:35:14,240 --> 00:35:16,550
我需要医生
I need a doctor.

609
00:35:17,280 --> 00:35:18,610
马上就有
Soon.

610
00:35:30,140 --> 00:35:31,630
那个哔哔声是什么
What's that beeping?

611
00:35:33,770 --> 00:35:35,860
你和其他人带上三个人质
You and the guys pick three hostages.

612
00:35:35,900 --> 00:35:37,110
为什么
Why?

613
00:35:37,670 --> 00:35:39,940
以防万一
We may need insurance.

614
00:35:40,380 --> 00:35:41,750
收好东西
Let's pack it up.

615
00:35:41,780 --> 00:35:44,410
约翰 他们激活了一个光弹
John, they've activated a light bomb.

616
00:35:44,450 --> 00:35:46,590
他们想要灭口
They're gonna kill the hostages.

617
00:35:51,280 --> 00:35:53,740
- 你要干嘛 - 按原计划 我们上楼
- What are you doing? - Sticking to the plan. We're going up.

618
00:35:53,790 --> 00:35:54,870
约翰 他们知道我们在这
John, they know we're here.

619
00:35:54,880 --> 00:35:56,380
他们也会料到我们会上楼
They're expecting us to come up the stairs.

620
00:35:56,420 --> 00:35:58,120
我们不可能活着走到二十五楼的
We won't make it to the 25th floor alive.

621
00:35:58,150 --> 00:35:59,490
他说的你也都听到了
You heard him.

622
00:35:59,520 --> 00:36:01,030
我们没有其他选择
We have no choice.

623
00:36:01,060 --> 00:36:03,230
是我没得选择
I don't have a choice.

624
00:36:04,830 --> 00:36:06,730
人质命悬一线
People's lives are in jeopardy.

625
00:36:06,760 --> 00:36:09,750
你中枪了 脑子里又塞了口香糖
You've been shot. Your head's full of bubble gum.

626
00:36:09,750 --> 00:36:11,340
